<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 13 at 2:20AM CST  by NWS QuadCities</headline>
<description>...Slick Travel Conditions...
An area of light to moderate snow will continue to move across
the area over the next several hours. Most areas will see an inch
or less of accumulation, but there will likely be a very narrow
band of 1 to 2 inch accumulations over portions of the area.
With the cold temperatures in the teens, untreated roadways will
become snow covered and slick.
Be prepared for slippery travel conditions if you`re planning to
travel early this morning.</description>
